<h1>District Import</h1>

<p>A CSV or Excel file can be used to import records. The first row should be the column name. The following columns are allowed.</p>

<ul>
  <% District.columns.each do |column| %>
    <li>
      <strong><%= column.name %></strong> -
      <%= column.type.to_s.titleize %> type
    </li>
  <% end %>
</ul>

<p>If <strong>id</strong> is supplied it will update the matching record, else if id column is missing <strong>name</strong> will be used to update the matching record instead of creating a new one.</p>

<%= form_for @district_import do |f| %>
  <div class="field">
    <%= f.file_field :file %>
  </div>
  <div class="buttons"><%= f.submit "Import", class: "btn btn-default" %></div>
<% end %>